Challenge 21: Next Greater Element
What to do:
Given a list of integers, find the next greater element for each number. The next greater element is the first number to the right that is larger. If there is none, print -1.
Example Input:
nums = [4, 5, 2, 10, 8]
Example Output:
[5, 10, 10, -1, -1]
Explanation:
•	Next greater of 4 is 5 
•	Next greater of 5 is 10 
•	Next greater of 2 is 10 
•	10 has no greater element to its right 
•	8 has no greater element to its right 
